  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">African Foundation for Development - Organisational Development Grant</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This grant will support a UK Diaspora organisation that helps Africans in the UK contribute effectively to lasting change &#x2013; particularly increased wealth &#x2013; in Africa.  AFFORD will contract a consultant to help them apply for funds. They will visit Southern Sudan and East Africa to build the connections and do the research needed for projects there. They will pay a designer to improve the website; and get new software to build a database of Africans with relevant skills and roles in Europe, supported by a consultant. 
This will mean the organisation will have enough funds to carry out projects in two new countries; and will have completed the preliminary studies. An improved and secure website will be where policy makers and those doing projects can find useful resources, case-studies and guidance. A new database will make AFFORD much more efficient in identifying people it needs to lobby for support, or people to help with projects. As a result of strengthening the organisation to share its learning and replicate its work in more countries, more people in Africa will ultimately find better jobs and enjoy a better standard of living.</narrative>
  </description>
